The former governor of Lagos State, Bola Tinubu is set to meet with members of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the House of Representatives. Tinubu, in a letter read by Speaker, Femi Gbajabiamila on Tuesday, said he will be hosting the lawmakers at the Transcorp Hilton, Abuja. In the letter, the former governor said he will be meeting with the lawmakers on Wednesday next week. Tinubu stated that he will be meeting with them as part of his consultation and to discuss policy with them. He said: “I want to share my vision for the nation with the caucus members and to hear likewise from them.” The national leader of the APC is one of the leading aspirants of the APC and despite the criticism over his age and his health status. Aside from his age, Mr Tinubu has been under criticism over his education qualification and source of his wealth.